# K.I.S.S. Principle (Keep It Simple Stupid)

## Core Philosophy
Always prioritize simplicity over complexity. Avoid over-engineering, unnecessary abstractions, or introducing heavy external dependencies when a straightforward native solution exists.

## Behavioral Mandates
* **Evaluate First:** Identify the absolute simplest path to achieve the core intent.
* **Propose Alternatives:** If an alternative approach exists that is significantly simpler to build or maintain, present that alternative to the user first before writing code.
